OL,3,CPolice officer labelled 'disgrace' for
OL,4,Chaving sex with woman on duty
OL,6,FThis number was linked back to the
OL,7,Fvulnerable young woman. It was then
OL,8,Funcovered that Arshad had been having
OL,9,Fsex with the victim while on duty.JMr
OL,10,FBaxter said: "Far detached from the
OL,11,Fknight in shining armour she initially
OL,12,Fthought he was, we suggest that she
OL,13,Fwas selected by him because of those
OL,14,Fvery vulnerabilities which caused him
OL,15,Fto first meet her and that he abused
OL,16,Fhis position as a serving police
OL,17,Fofficer, gaining her trust, in order
OL,18,Fto sleep with her.
OL,20,F"His concern was not her wellbeing,
OL,21,Fbut rather his own sexual desires."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/11
